This paper focuses on using a dual-layer attention-based neural network to predict stock prices based on financial news. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category (cs.CL) as it involves text processing. Additionally, it involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract relevant news, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques to predict stock prices, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category.
